This is Perl module Text::XliffParser.

INSTALLATION

Text::XliffParser installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set up,
you should just be able to do

    % cpan Text::XliffParser

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Text::XliffParser documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Text::XliffParser

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

